pr_review_comment_body:
@szha - that's a great list that chinakook has compiled. I feel like some of those items need to be added to /examples. Some could be added to ecosystem. I'm not sure if I should do that in this PR though.
It would make more sense for contributors to propose the addition of their work to the ecosystem or examples page(s), wouldn't it?

@thomelane - I've added those three in my pending update.

I'd do it as a class attribute.

```python
class KeyMapDB:
    @staticmethod
    @abstractmethod
    def key_fn(value: bytes) -> bytes:
        raise NotImplementedError

class HashTrie(KeyMapDB):
    key_fn = staticmethod(keccak)
```

move the sc.stop to
after {
}

to make sure it won't affect other test result when it fail

